Date of Birth: May 9, 1898<br/>
Birthplace: Salt Lake City, Utah, USA<br/>
Ordained apostle: Oct. 11, 1962<br/>
Death: November 27, 1982<br/>
<br/>
Born May 9, 1898, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, to Nathan William Tanner and Sarah Edna Brown.
Sustained as Assistant to the Twelve Oct. 8, 1960, at age 62; ordained apostle Oct. 11, 1962, at age 64;
sustained as second counselor to President David 0. McKay Oct. 4,1963; sustained as second counselor to President Joseph Fielding Smith Jan. 23,1970; sustained as first counselor to President Harold B. Lee July 7,1972;
sustained as first counselor to President Spencer W. Kimball Dec. 30,1973;
died Nov. 27, 1982, at Salt Lake City, Salt Lake Co., Utah, at age 84.